<TEXT>
<P>
   FORGET TV'S `SURVIVOR.'
</P>
<P>
   HERE'S A SURVIVAL GUIDE FOR REAL LIFE.
</P>
<P>
   Life is tough for those people on ``Survivor.'' First they were
dumped into the sea. Then, on the island, they had to build
shelter, find food (rats, anyone?) and start a fire without
matches.
</P>
<P>
   But that's just a TV show. What if you found yourself adrift at
sea IN REAL LIFE? Would you know what to do?
</P>
<P>
   You would if you had read ``The WORST-CASE SCENARIO Survival
Handbook,'' a best seller designed to get you through those times
when life suddenly takes a turn for the worse.
</P>
<P>
   If you haven't read it, don't panic. An eight-part series from
the book is available now _ just in time for the summer disaster
season. Each 500-word excerpt INCLUDES ART:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CAUGHT IN A `TITANIC' SITUATION? HOW TO SURVIVE ADRIFT AT SEA &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOWDY, SMOKEY. WHAT TO DO IF YOU COME FACE-TO-FACE WITH A
BEAR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   `HE'S GOT A GUN!' HOW TO SURVIVE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CAN IT STRIKE TWICE? WHY YOU SHOULD WATCH OUT FOR LIGHTNING &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DIDN'T ENJOY `JAWS'? HOW TO FEND OFF A SHARK &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LOOK BEFORE YOU LEAP: HOW TO SURVIVE A JUMP INTO WATER FROM A
BRIDGE OR CLIFF &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SNAKE NOT CHARMED? HOW TO SURVIVE AN ATTACK &LR;  &QL;
</P>
