<P>
   MEDICARE-HMOS (Washington) _ Managed-care health plans warn that
low government reimbursements will result in 711,000 Medicare
beneficiaries losing coverage next year. This is the managed-care's
latest campaign to get Congress to hike payments to plans that
offer health care and a prescription drug benefit to 6.3 million of
Medicare's 39 million beneficiaries. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-FUNDING (Washington) _ Reps. Henry A. Waxman and Tom Coburn
on Thursday defended their decision to cut San Francisco's share of
federal AIDS funding by one-fourth over five years, saying the city
has been ``overcompensated'' in the past. Bipartisan legislation
introduced Thursday ``slowly gets rid of marked discrepancies'' in
funding for 51 cities ravaged by the epidemic, said Waxman. By JUDY
HOLLAND.
</P>
