<SLUG> BC-FILM-JORDAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JORDAN FILM UNUSUAL CHOICE FOR LARGE-FORMAT IMAX THEATER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ALYSON WARD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The Fort Worth Museum of Science and
History's IMAX screen is usually reserved for the educational. You
go there to see films about butterflies and dolphins, earthquakes
and volcanoes. You don't go there expecting to celebrate sports
heroes to a jock-jams pop music beat.
</P>
<P>
   So the museum's newest IMAX film, ``Michael Jordan to the Max''
_ added to a film rotation that includes ``Dolphins'' and ``T-Rex:
Back to the Cretaceous'' _ is an unusual choice. But the 45-minute
portrait of the basketball superstar is also a good choice. Though
not specifically educational, the film is inspiring, entertaining
and ideal for summer viewing.
</P>
<P>
   The film follows Jordan through the final games of his
basketball career _ the 1998 NBA playoffs, where he led the Chicago
Bulls to the team's sixth championship. It also offers a glimpse of
Jordan's early days, his short-lived baseball career and his impact
in the basketball world.
</P>
<P>
   Jordan's impact, of course, goes beyond the basketball world _
and that's the film's main message. ``Michael Jordan to the Max''
is the first IMAX film to feature an individual. Usually the
large-format films are dedicated to large-format subjects _
mountains, oceans, rain forests. But if there's anyone the
larger-than-life portrayal fits, it's Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   Phil Jackson, Jordan's coach when he played for the Bulls, calls
him ``a real-life hero.'' This film, which debuted worldwide in
May, shows the talent, determination, work ethic and dignity that
made the class-act Jordan the athlete of the century.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Film: ``Michael Jordan to the Max''
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 4 on a 1-5 scale
</P>
<P>
   Length: 45 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Rated: Not rated
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
