<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-EXTREME-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THEY ATTEMPT THE IMPOSSIBLE TO PROVE THAT IT'S POSSIBLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ALYSON WARD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Most of us feel pretty athletic if we run a few miles or master
in-line skating in the driveway. We talk about hitting a runner's
high or finding the zone as if we're really accomplishing something
extraordinary.
</P>
<P>
   All it takes is a movie like ``Extreme'' to wipe those notions
away. The IMAX film features world-class athletes who have
conquered extreme sports _ surfing, windsurfing, skiing,
snowboarding, rock climbing and ice climbing. They're risk-takers,
top-of-their-sport champions who attempt the impossible to prove
that it's possible.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to have fear; fear is the thing that keeps you sane,''
says ice climber Barry Blanchard, who proceeds to climb his way up
the Delphine Glacier in Canada, one of the world's most spectacular
icefalls (a frozen waterfall). Sanity is debatable, and Blanchard
looks fearless _ but fear is a given in extreme sports.
</P>
<P>
   Big-wave surfers in Hawaii tackle some of the biggest waves ever
surfed. The surfers hit the North Shore of Hawaii just as El Nino
did, in 1998; the unprecedented waves canceled official surfing
competitions, but the surfers in ``Extreme'' went out there anyway
and rode 40-foot waves _ something surfers had never accomplished
before.
</P>
<P>
   Also in ``Extreme'': champion wind surfers in Hawaii take on
some of Maui's highest winds, skiers maneuver down almost-vertical
slopes in Alaska, and rock climbers dangle high above the ground in
southern Utah.
</P>
<P>
   Because of the IMAX screen's immense size, viewers can imagine
they're in the middle of it all, hanging from rocks or gliding down
steep slopes with the athletes. The experience is simultaneously
daunting and inspiring. It's clear that these extreme athletes are
part of an exclusive club. The rest of us will have to settle for
some waterskis and a lake and the illusion of greatness.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Film: ``Extreme''
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 3 1/2 on a 1-5 scale
</P>
<P>
   Length: 40 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Rated: Not rated
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
