the heat, the glaciers in Seward, Alaska, aren't melting at all. So
if you're looking for a cooling escape from the summer heat, go
north _ all the way to Seward, where the scenery's beautiful, the
town's laid-back, and the moose might be grazing right across from
your cabin. By MICHAEL GERST. Story has moved in ``t'' travel
