<P>
   IRAN-JEWS (Hamadan) _ This is where Esther, the Jewish queen of
Persia, is reputed to be buried, a town once a center of Jewish
life. Now there are 35 Jews left. Here, as elsewhere in Iran, a
once-thriving community is worried. A verdict is expected Saturday
in the spy trial of 13 Jews in the Iranian city of Shiraz and,
according to Jewish leaders, the case has made life so unsettled
that up to half of the remaining Iranian Jews will emigrate in the
next year or so. By Susan Sachs. (The story has moved in ``i'' news
file.)
