passed a Republican-drafted plan to add a prescription drug benefit
to Medicare, one of the biggest changes to the health program for
the aged since its creation in 1965. House Speaker Dennis Hastert,
left, flanked by fellow Republican members of the House, addressed
a news conference on the steps of the Capitol, Thursday. (Stephen
Crowley/The New York Times)
