   (NYT15) UNDATED -- June 29, 2000 -- ALICE-NEEL-PAINTINGS --
Alice Neel made some of the best paintings of the 20th century and
added in particular to its store of great portraiture, as
demonstrated by the illuminating but truncated retrospective of her
work at the Whitney Museum of American Art. Neel's 1970 portrait of
Gregory Battcock and David Bourdon are in the Whitney Museum
