   (NYT13) BENNINGTON, Vt. -- June 29, 2000 -- BENNINGTON-TRAVEL-1
-- The First Congregational Church in Bennington, Vt. Completed in
1806, it is every inch the traditional white New England clapboard
church-on-the-green. The burial ground behind the church contains
Robert Frost's grave, as well as the resting places of
Revolutionary soldiers and several Vermont governors.(Paul O.
Boisvert/The New York Times)
