turquoise water and white sands, combine to produce a compelling
array of colors. Dingle has 1,200 residents and 52 pubs. In Gaelic,
Dingle means ``fortress,'' appropriate enough given how the town is
sheltered by the mountains on one side and the Atlantic on the
other. (Glenn Whipp/The Los Angeles Daily News)
</P>
