Greg Maddux jersey.
</P>
<P>
   ``First of all I find out Maddux is sick and not pitching
tonight,'' Vargas sighed while nibbling a bit nervously on a piece
of red licorice. ``Then I'm getting a LOT of heckling about the
shirt. They yell `Take the jersey off,' `You shouldn't be here,'
and `Rocker sucks!'
</P>
<P>
   ``It's guilt by association,'' Vargas laughingly concluded.
</P>
<P>
   Even Rocker's pre-game schoomzing with fans made some of them
just hate him more.
</P>
<P>
   ``Usually you can go down near the field during batting practice
and get autographs, but because of all this Rocker stuff, they
weren't letting people down there,'' complained Mets season ticket
holder Michael Conslato, pointing to his disappointed 5-year-old
son. ``I wish he'd go to the minors and not ruin our whole
weekend.''
</P>
<P>
   If only he'd been a little less cooperative.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
