<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, JUNE 30
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-DRUGS-LOBBY-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 27
about lobbying by the drug industry against the Clinton
administration's Medicare prescription drug proposal included an
outdated reference to the Alliance for Lung Cancer Advocacy,
Support and Education. The group was indeed a member of Citizens
for Better Medicare, a group largely financed by the pharmaceutical
industry. But last week it severed the connection because it was
uncomfortable with the group's aggressive lobbying against
expansion of Medicare benefits, a senior executive of the alliance
said.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-NY-TALL-SHIPS (moved on Thursday, June 29) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, June 29
about preparations for the festival of tall ships and military
vessels in New York Harbor next week misstated the mile-per-hour
equivalent of 10 knots, the speed limit to be imposed for pleasure
boats. Ten knots is 11.5 miles per hour, not 8. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
